Question: Java file read problem: :I have a java problem. I am trying  to read a txt file which has a variable number of integers per line, and for each line I need to sum every second integer! I am using scanner to read integers, but can't work out when a line is done. Can anyone help pls?
Please using this api: StringTokenizer.nextToken.
Answer:
<<<api>>>: StringTokenizer.nextToken
<<<code>>>:
StringTokenizer st = new StringTokenizer(line);
while(st.hasMoreTokens()) {
    int i = Integer.parseInt(st.nextToken());
    if(i % 2 == 0) {
        sum += i;
    }
}
<<<explanation>>>:
The StringTokenizer class is used to break a string into tokens. A token is a piece of a string that is separated by a delimiter. The delimiter can be a character or a string. The StringTokenizer class has a constructor that takes a string and a delimiter as arguments. The hasMoreTokens() method returns true if there are more tokens left to be read. The nextToken() method returns the next token.
